# CrowdSec – optional environment variables
#
# Copy to stack.env if you want to override defaults.
#
# This stack runs the CrowdSec Security Engine in a container and persists its
# configuration and data in Docker volumes. You still need to configure which
# logs CrowdSec should analyze (see the stack README and CrowdSec docs).
#
# Docs:
# - Docker installation: https://docs.crowdsec.net/u/getting_started/installation/docker/
# - Hub collections:     https://docs.crowdsec.net/docs/next/hub/overview
#

# TZ/locale: use shared.env (see documents/SHARED-RESOURCES.md)

# Optional: group ID used by CrowdSec inside the container.
# Set this to a group that has read access to your log files if you mount
# host logs into the container.
# GID=1000

# Optional: default hub collections to install on start.
# Override this to include collections that match your stack (Caddy, SSH, etc.).
# Example (SANITIZED – adjust to your needs):
# COLLECTIONS="crowdsecurity/linux"

# Optional: path to acquis.yaml on the host (where CrowdSec gets log source config).
# Default: ${HOME}/.config/crowdsec/acquis.yaml. Copy acquis.yaml.example there and edit.
# When deploying from Portainer, set this to the absolute path to your acquis file.
# CROWDSEC_ACQUIS_PATH=/home/youruser/.config/crowdsec/acquis.yaml

